2. In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires- Interpretation
"Board" means the Board of Veterinary Surgery established under section three;
"Director" means the Director of Veterinary Services;
"practice of veterinary surgery or medicine" includes the performance of any
operation and the giving of and providing of any treatment, test, advice,
diagnosis or attendance such as is usually performed, given or provided by
veterinary surgeons;
"the Register" means the Register of Veterinary Surgeons provided for in section
nine;
"to register" means to enter in the Register the particulars required by section nine;
"registered veterinary surgeon" means a person whose name appears in the
Register as a veterinary surgeon.
